-- Zambia, Botswana Face $130 Shortfall for Bridge, Times Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-04-02T10:15:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/zambia-botswana-face-130-shortfall-for-bridge-times-reports.html
Zambia  and Botswana face a $130
million shortfall for the construction of the Kazungula Bridge
which will link the neighboring countries, the Lusaka  Times 
said, citing Zambia’s works minister, Yamfya Mukanga.  Both countries are seeking funds to build the bridge across
the Zambezi River, the Times said on its website. It didn’t say
when construction is expected to begin.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at  in Harare
at   blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 